  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nI think in case the connection between reader and laptop was interrupted, then there is no chance to continue\r\n\r\n1. get new empty card\r\n2. start the new keys flow\r\n3. when being on repeat PIN screen, stay there for a while (10 min or so)\r\n4. try to repeat PIN\r\n\r\nWhat logs are saying:\r\n\r\n```\r\n1 currFlow=FirstRunNewUserNewKeycardKeys currState=KeycardRepeatPin\r\nDBG 2022-08-05 10:54:01.081+03:00 keycardResumeFlow                          topics=\"keycard-service\" tid=895614 file=service.nim:117 flowType=2 payload=\"{\\\"overwrite\\\":true,\\\"mnemonic-length\\\":12,\\\"pin\\\":\\\"000000\\\",\\\"new-pin\\\":\\\"000000\\\",\\\"new-puk\\\":\\\"743186816266\\\"}\" response=ok\r\nkeycard - init failed scard: Service not available.\r\nDBG 2022-08-05 10:54:01.138+03:00 keycard_signal                             topics=\"keycard-service\" tid=895614 file=service.nim:91 response=\"{\\\"type\\\":\\\"keycard.flow-result\\\",\\\"event\\\":{\\\"error\\\":\\\"scard: Service not available.\\\"}}\"\r\nDBG 2022-08-05 10:54:01.139+03:00 on_keycard_response                        topics=\"app-controller\" tid=895614 file=module.nim:240 currFlow=FirstRunNewUserNewKeycardKeys currState=KeycardRepeatPin\r\n```\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1436\" alt=\"Screenshot 2022-08-05 at 10 54 30\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/82375995/183030171-8d53068a-c1e6-4870-a231-d234189c8c7d.png\">\r\n",
